<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-27T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="571" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d571">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/710c: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-27T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            27, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Impress upon the Chinese Government importance of formal approval of
                                the plan for operation of Siberian railways and prompt designation
                                of representatives on commission. The plan as submitted has now been
                                formally approved by Great Britain and France as well as by the
                                United States and Japan and consequently has gone too far for any
                                modification of principle.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>